name: PDFSaveOptions

properties.name: alphaChannels
properties.description: If true, the alpha channels are saved.

properties.name: layers
properties.description: If true, the layers are saved.

properties.name: annotations
properties.description: If true, the annotations are saved.

properties.name: spotColors
properties.description: If true, the spot colors are saved.

properties.name: embedColorProfile
properties.description: If true, the color profile is embedded in the document.

properties.name: downgradeColorProfile
properties.description: DEPRECATED, ( should the embedded color profile be downgraded to version 2 )

properties.name: transparency
properties.description: DEPRECATED.

properties.name: interpolation
properties.description: DEPRECATED. ( use image interpolation? )

properties.name: vectorData
properties.description: DEPRECATED. ( include vector data )

properties.name: embedFonts
properties.description: DEPRECATED. ( embed fonts? Only valid if a text layer is included )

properties.name: useOutlines
properties.description: DEPRECATED. ( use outlines for text? Only valid if vector data is included )

properties.name: encoding
properties.description: The encoding method to use.

properties.name: jpegQuality
properties.description: The quality of the produced image. Valid only for JPEG-encoded PDF documents. Range: 0 to 12.

properties.name: presetFile
properties.description: The preset file to use for settings; overrides other settings.

properties.name: PDFStandard
properties.description: The PDF standard to make the document compatible with.

properties.name: PDFCompatibility
properties.description: The PDF version to make the document compatible with.

properties.name: description
properties.description: Description of the save options in use.

properties.name: preserveEditing
properties.description: If true, allows users to reopen the PDF in Photoshop with native Photoshop data intact.

properties.name: embedThumbnail
properties.description: If true, includes a small preview image in Acrobat.

properties.name: optimizeForWeb
properties.description: If true, improves performance of PDFs on Web servers.

properties.name: view
properties.description: If true, opens the saved PDF in Acrobat.

properties.name: downSample
properties.description: The downsample method to use.

properties.name: downSampleSize
properties.description: The size (in pixels per inch) to downsample images to if they exceed the value specified for 'down sample size limit'.

properties.name: downSampleSizeLimit
properties.description: Limits downsampling or subsampling to images that exceed this value (in pixels per inch).

properties.name: tileSize
properties.description: The compression option. Valid only when encoding is JPEG2000.

properties.name: convertToEightBit
properties.description: If true, converts a 16-bit image to 8-bit for better compatibility with other applications.

properties.name: colorConversion
properties.description: If true, converts the color profile to the destination profile.

properties.name: destinationProfile
properties.description: Describes the final RGB or CMYK output device, such as a monitor or press standard.

properties.name: profileInclusionPolicy
properties.description: If true, shows which profiles to include.

properties.name: outputCondition
properties.description: An optional comment field for inserting descriptions of the output condition. The text is stored in the PDF/X file.

properties.name: outputConditionID
properties.description: The identifier for the output condition.

properties.name: registryName
properties.description: The URL where the output condition is registered.

description: Options for saving a document in PDF format.
